<TITLE> India's SPICE chooses Bangladesh for international market debut </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 22 (bdnews24.com)  Indian 'SPICE' brand mobiles made their first foray into the international market by launching four handsets in Bangladesh on Tuesday. "We chose to enter the international market with Bangladesh as the country offers great opportunities for mobile handset companies with huge untapped penetration," Kunal Ahoja, CEO of Spice Mobiles Ltd, said at the launch. Mehboob Chowdhury, chairman of the South Asian Mobile Forum, said: "A greater cooperation is needed among the mobile phone manufacturers and operators of South Asia." "I congratulate Spice, a major brand of the region, for focusing their attention on Bangladesh and hope they may work for the benefit of all the South Asian nations." True Distributions Ltd has brought the four Spice handsets to Bangladesh, showcased at the launch event at Radisson Water Garden Hotel in the capital. Mahboob Ahmed, commission secretary of BTRC and Ghalib Ahmed Ansari, CEO of True Distributions Ltd, were among the guests.
